com.yworks.yfiles.layout.multipage

Interface INodeInfo


  • public interface INodeInfo
    This interface offers access to information associated with a node.

    The information can be either obtained from MultiPageLayoutResult.getNodeInfo(Node) or LayoutContext.getNodeInfo(Node).

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      • getPageNo

        This information is first available after the layout run.
        Returns:
        the page of the associated node

      • getReferencingNode

        Node getReferencingNode()
        Gets the node that refers to the one associated with this info object.

        More precisely, if the node associated with this info object

        • is a connector node, this method returns the matching connector node,
        • is a proxy node, it returns the corresponding proxy reference node,
        • is a proxy reference node, it returns the corresponding proxy node,
        • or otherwise, it returns null.
        Returns:
        the referencing node
        See Also:
        NodeType.CONNECTOR, NodeType.PROXY, NodeType.PROXY_REFERENCE

      • getRepresentedNode

        Node getRepresentedNode()
        Gets the node of the input graph that is represented by the node associated with this info object.

        Note that, for the special nodes inserted to guarantee that no information is lost, there are no corresponding nodes in the input graph. Hence, special nodes are mapped to common nodes in the following way:

        • A connector node is mapped to the common node connected to the matching connector.
        • A proxy node is mapped to the associated common node (i.e., the proxy is a copy of that node).
        • A proxy reference node is not mapped to any node, and, thus this method returns null for such nodes.
         
        All nodes of the page graphs are created by the layout algorithm, the input graph remains unchanged. Matching elements are mapped to the same element ID, see MultiPageLayout.NODE_ID_DPKEY, MultiPageLayout.EDGE_ID_DPKEY, MultiPageLayout.NODE_LABEL_ID_DPKEY and MultiPageLayout.EDGE_LABEL_ID_DPKEY. This method always returns a node of the input graph!
        Returns:
        the represented node

      • getType

        Returns:
        the type of the node
